=====================
Variables & Data Type
=====================

- Variable
  --------
  - a container to store value
  - Syntax
    - <Data type> <variable name>;  // variable definations
    - <Data type> <variable name> = <value>;  // variable declaration
    

- Types of variable
  -----------------
  - Local Variable
    - Declared the body of a method
    - Scope of variable is within the body of that method
    
  - Instance Variable
    - variable declared inside the class but outside all methods
    - Scope of variable is inside entire class body
      i.e., inside class methods also
      
  - Static Variable
    - Declared using "static" keyword
    - cannot be local variable
      i.e., it can only be instance variable
    - Accessable inside static methods only 
  

- Data type
  ---------
  - Specifies different sizes and type of values 
    that can be stored inside a variable
  - should be explictly defined in java

- Types of Data type
  ------------------
  - Boolean
    - binary value (true/false)
  - Char
    - Single Unicode character
  - String
    - set of character
    - Ex: String name = "Himanshu";
  - Int
    - 32 bit integer value
  - Long
    - 64 bit integer value
    - must add "L" at the end of number;
    - Ex: long empNo = 123456789L;
  - Double
    - 64 bit decimal value
    - recommended to use "D" after value
      - will not show error without "D"
    - Ex: double marks = 92.5;
      or  double marks = 92.5D;




